The paper deals with the impact of spatial, temporal, and amplitude resolution on the perceptual quality of compressed video, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the modeling of quality decay rates, which involves information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, subjective quality tests were carried out on a mobile device, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
